Class ChatMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opentok.android.ui.textchat.widget.ChatMessage

  • public class ChatMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines the chat message object that you pass into the TextChatFragment.addMessage(ChatMessage msg) method.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ChatMessage

        public ChatMessage(java.lang.String senderId,
           java.lang.String senderAlias,
           java.lang.String text)
        Construct a chat message that includes a message string, a sender identifier, and a sender alias.
        Parameters:
        senderId - The unique ID string for the sender of the of the message. The TextChatFragment uses this ID to group messages from the same sender in the user interface.
        senderAlias - The string (alias) identifying the sender of the message.
        text - The text of the message.

      • ChatMessage

        public ChatMessage(java.lang.String senderId,
           java.lang.String sender,
           java.lang.String text,
           ChatMessage.MessageStatus status)
        Construct a chat message that includes a message string, a sender identifier, a sender alias and the sent/recieved status.
        Parameters:
        senderId - The unique ID string for the sender of the of the message. The TextChatFragment uses this ID to group messages from the same sender in the user interface.
        sender - The string (alias) identifying the sender of the message.
        text - The text of the message.
        status - Whether the message was sent or received.
